pr_body:
Multiple fixes and enhancements to Ethernet and LLC decoders. Summary of changes:
+ VLAN tags are organized into 2 new classes: VLANtag8021Q and VLANtagISL, contained in a new list field "Ethernet.vlan_tags";
+ MPLS labels are similarly a new class MPLSlabel, contained in a new list field "Ethernet.mpls_labels";
+ support IEEE 802.1Q double tagging (aka QinQ);
+ Ethernet/IEEE 802.3 Ethernet can be constructed with MPLS labels and/or VLAN tags;
+ fixed construction of LLC with SAP/SNAP headers and data encapsulation;
+ fixed parsing of Cisco ISL VLAN tag (was off by 1 bit);
+ correctly compute len() of Ethernet with tags/labels and LLC;
+ compute 802.3 Ethernet Frame Check Sequence (FCS), recognize trailer bytes;
+ added a bunch of unit tests.

Changes are backward compatible, except the following:
+ LLC is now a layer. This matches Wireshark representation, and I believe it was meant to be this way originally in dpkt, but eventually llc.py unpacking code was moved into ethernet.py. I guess it was moved to deal with circular referencing between the two modules. I found a solution that avoids these issues.
+ As a result of the above change, LLC.data that is now properly decoded to the next layer (previously one had to explicitly cast it, e.g. ip.IP(llc.data)).

Fixes #59, #83, #89, #140, #148

This hack is only needed for pip versions older than 9.
Fixes #301, fixes #321.

@jaraco I have little experience in writing PEP 508 markers, so please review it.

I suggest support for Field(required=False) is added to service_objects fields. I would like to be able to do something like this.
```
class ServiceExample(Service):
    some_model = ModelField(model_class='SomeModel', required=False)

    def process(self):
        some_model = self.cleaned_data['some_model']
        if some_model:
            'do a'
        else:
            'do b'
```
I would say updating docs is not needed since is expected behavior of a field - but maybe a small mention wouldn't hurt. 

Please let me know what you think.

#1288 
@neubig at your convenience please take a look at the dropout implementation, which seems to be extremely slow.

Reported by @zhiyong1997 : Without dropout, one epoch takes ~11 seconds on GPU, but when one dropout is added (only to the layer before logits calculation), the time becomes ~18 seconds. By contrast, when three different dropouts are added in TF fold at the same time, the time only turns from ~13s to ~15s, which is ~30s for dynet.

@mcg1969 @mingwandroid 

I'm including this in the `4.1.6` release to go out shortly.

This changes the "max total time" from about 3.2 seconds to 6.5 seconds.  Meaning the final sleep has a time of 3.2 sec, with the total cumulative time before failure being 6.5 sec.

Added support for using a surrogate vgg16 model. User should be able to use a pretrained vgg16 model, just as they could use resnet, or inception.

I feel like this would be useful because many articles have been published that use the feature extraction features of VGG-16 for other analysis such as image segmentation, multi-label classifications etc. Thus, this would be a useful thing to have.

